            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p> In respect to <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0229">the account of the
                            Macleaneâ€™s</title>
                    </bibl> if you can give the abstract of the extent of
                    their dominions when in their Glory, the means how they came by <placeName ref="pl0729">Mull</placeName>, what sieges the castles of <placeName ref="pl0682">Aros</placeName>, <placeName ref="pl0684">Duwart</placeName> or
                        <placeName ref="pl0738">Donen</placeName> sustained; or <placeName ref="pl0739">the fort on the little isle of Carnbergh</placeName>. I shall
                    be glad to know; for as my Tour is just finished I shall also finish my queries
                    for some weeks, &amp; give myself a holyday after my Long labor.<note type="editorial">The first edition of Pennant's <bibl type="editorial">
                            <title ref="bi0008">
                                <hi rend="italic">Tour in Scotland and Hebrides
                                    1772</hi>
                            </title>
                        </bibl> was published in 1774. However
                        Pennant's ongoing queries in this letter relating to the history of the
                        Hebrides, suggest that the finished work referred to above was the revised
                            <bibl type="editorial">
                            <title ref="bi0004">
                                <hi rend="italic">Tour in
                                    Scotland 1769</hi>
                            </title>, 3<hi rend="superscript">rd</hi> edn.
                            (Warrington: 1774)</bibl>.</note> The sooner the above arrive the more
                    welcome to</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                            obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName>. Jan 30<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1774.</dateline>
            </div>
